26/08/2005
SOFIA, Bulgaria -- The defence ministry announced on Thursday (25 August) that air forces of 14 NATO members and eight partner countries are taking part in a joint exercise. The 12-day drill, focused on helicopter aviation, includes live flying and will test the capability of participating air forces to work together in peacekeeping operations and rescue missions. Some 1,500 personnel and 68 aircraft, including two AWACS planes, are involved in the exercise, led by NATO's Allied Air Component Command in Izmir, Turkey. (bTV, AP - 25/08/05)
